to the editor peter schweizer all they can be except american op ed feb 18 argues that an american foreign legion would help resolve the military 's manpower problems but it would also worsen existing problems in civil military relations many already complain of a gap between the country and its professional relatively isolated military and as a captain in the united states army i see that few americans are aware of the military 's extensive list of deployments but who would care if the american foreign legion spent 10 more years in kosovo inherent in the citizen soldier is a mechanism for accountability giving the government a way to reduce public involvement is to forfeit our duty to be engaged in the decision making process we must remain accountable for military action undertaken in the name of our country jason dempsey new york feb 19 2003

